column5: Joepa walleye fishing was slow. lots of small northern. largest was 36 inches,about 11 pounds. very hot with rain 2 days. the walleye all had minnows in them. we used gold erie dearies tipped with nightcrawlers. good luck mike
Thanks Mike, sure hope it gets better at end of month. joepa
joepa let us know how you did at camp ronoda. also if you get a clear night you need to check the stars. thanks mike e
